20/03/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano announced that the government will clamp down on organised crime and tighten security in view of the operation to disarm the Iraqi regime.
Late Tuesday (18 March), Nano urged his ministers to adopt measures to maintain public order, advising them that Tirana's participation in the US-led coalition could make it a target for terrorists.
He added that authorities would speed up efforts to uproot organised crime, considered a source terrorist financing.
Armed Forces Chief of Staff Gen Pellumb Qazimi said the army is closely following developments in Iraq and will react in case of emergency.
Albania is among 30 countries that joined the US-led anti-terrorist coalition and has offered logistical support.
(AP, ATA, ATV - 19/03/03)
